Hi there! Ever wanted to run your PNGTuber natively in Vnyan? Well, now you can!

This logic loop will not work properly unless you configure a few things to support it. Here's what you'll need to get started:

1. Import 4 "states" of pictures as props* that your PNGTuber will use. Currently the graph is set up to support states as follows (change these to suit your needs on the toggle prop nodes on the far right side of the graph)
	- Berypng4: eyes closed and mouth open	- Berypng3: eyes open and mouth open
	- Berypng2: eyes closed mouth closed	- Berypng1: eyes open mouth closed
	
	*align the props to the world but do not lock them to always face the camera. You'll need to mess with the offest in the prop import menu to get placement just right.

2. Setup your cameras. The first one can be whatever fits your placement best, and the second is a slightly more "zoomed in" version of the same camera. you will swap between these two cams when you speak to help give you PNGTuber a bit more life.

	- the "Camera 10" node on the right side of the nodegraph is the zoomed in version, and the "Camera 1" node is the base.

3. Go to the settings menu and click on Misc (this is also where you can setup and save your camera). You'll need to setup a new position for your vtuber as we flatten and shrink it to serve as a source of colliders for other redeems.

	- Leave the default position slot as is, but go to slot Pos 1 and turn on the gizmo to move around your avatar's base coordinates.
	- You might have to zoom out to see the gizmo (it looks like the standard XYZ rotational sphere controls in blender.
	- Make sure to set it as "show" in the same menus you tweak your positions settings).
	- update all the Load Avatar nodes with your appropriate VTuber files. This is necessary for your PNGTuber to have collision

4. Have fun!There's probably more I forgot, but these are the big ones. Let me know if you have questions and I'm happy to help, I'm best reached on Discord (Berymuch), but you can also MSG me on Bluesky :3
